- Who is it?
- It's me.

38:33.353 --> 38:34.855
Oh, come in.

38:35.589 --> 38:37.091
I ran back before the crowd got in.

38:37.157 --> 38:39.501
- Well, how was it?
- You were only sensational.

38:39.560 --> 38:41.301
Thank you, Dick, for everything.

38:41.361 --> 38:43.568
The flowers, your help,
the way you conducted.

38:43.630 --> 38:44.973
You're welcome.

38:45.532 --> 38:47.739
Joyce, would you like to go out tonight?

38:47.801 --> 38:50.748
- Have a drink maybe?
- Oh, Dick, I'm sorry.

38:50.804 --> 38:52.408
But you know me, opening night.

38:52.472 --> 38:54.884
I'm going right home,
get a hamburger and crawl into bed.

38:54.942 --> 38:57.252
- Give me a rain check, will you?
- Sure.

38:57.311 --> 39:00.315
- How about tomorrow? It's Sunday.
- Oh, that's right.

39:00.380 --> 39:03.486
I tell you what, come over around 4:00
and I'll make you a nice cup of tea.

39:03.550 --> 39:05.621
4:00? I'll be there.

39:07.221 --> 39:09.030
More flowers.

39:09.089 --> 39:11.000
Dick, they're perfectly beautiful.

39:11.058 --> 39:12.537
Thank you again.

39:13.627 --> 39:14.833
There.

39:15.462 --> 39:18.671
- Well, sit down.
- Thanks.

39:23.303 --> 39:25.408
I hate Saturday night openings, don't you?

39:25.472 --> 39:26.576
Yeah.

39:26.640 --> 39:30.588
Waiting till Monday for the notices
is kind of like a Chinese execution.

39:36.350 --> 39:38.455
Is something troubling you, Dick?

39:39.686 --> 39:40.858
Look, Joyce,

39:42.222 --> 39:46.136
I can't say this the way I want to,
so I'll just say it plain.

39:46.927 --> 39:48.235
I'm in love with you.

39:48.295 --> 39:51.742
And I've been in love with you a long time
and I don't know what to do about it.

39:51.798 --> 39:53.106
Do you...

39:54.134 --> 39:57.172
- Are you serious?
- I'd like to marry you.

39:58.238 --> 40:00.946
Well, I guess that's all there is to it.

40:01.708 --> 40:03.813
Dick, come here.

40:07.547 --> 40:11.723
I can't tell you how sweet that was,
your telling me just that way.

40:11.785 --> 40:14.527
You're one of the nicest persons
I've ever known.

40:14.588 --> 40:17.660
But nice as it is to hear,
it just doesn't make sense.

40:17.724 --> 40:20.432
But why does it have to make sense?

40:20.494 --> 40:23.634
Because being in love
is more than just saying it,

40:23.697 --> 40:26.678
or wanting to be, or thinking you are.

40:26.733 --> 40:28.735
And your being in love with me
is impossible.

40:28.802 --> 40:31.544
- Believe me, it is.
- Why?

40:31.605 --> 40:33.983
Well, mathematics.

40:34.041 --> 40:36.351
I'm 33, you're 23.

40:36.410 --> 40:38.219
What difference does that make?

40:38.278 --> 40:41.282
Dick, when a woman's 33,

40:41.348 --> 40:44.522
a day's a difference, a week's a difference,
a month's a difference.

40:44.584 --> 40:46.996
Ten years, that's a century.

40:50.357 --> 40:53.361
Well, I guess that's that.

40:55.095 --> 40:58.599
How would you like your tea?
With or without sugar?

40:58.665 --> 41:00.474
Two lumps are fine for me.

41:02.502 --> 41:05.506
<i>Sugar or no,
I was a very bitter young man.</i>

41:05.572 --> 41:09.042
<i>The girl of my dreams didn't love me
and all the world was sad and dreary.</i>

41:09.443 --> 41:10.979
<i>In black despair, I decided to do</i>

41:11.044 --> 41:13.251
<i>what every young fellow
with a broken heart does.</i>

41:13.680 --> 41:16.092
<i>I decided to go to the movies.</i>

41:16.149 --> 41:18.925
<i>But I was in no mood to be alone
and so in search of company,</i>

41:18.986 --> 41:21.227
<i>I dropped in on an old friend,</i>

41:21.288 --> 41:22.460
<i>Ben Feiner.</i>

41:24.424 --> 41:27.564
- Hello, Dorothy. Is Ben home?
- No, but come in.

41:27.627 --> 41:28.799
Thanks.

41:30.397 --> 41:32.468
I'm sorry. Ben went out.

41:32.532 --> 41:35.604
Say, when did you get so big?

41:35.669 --> 41:37.979
Oh, I don't know. Just lately, I guess.

41:38.038 --> 41:41.144
Well, I thought maybe Ben would like
to see a movie or something.

41:41.208 --> 41:44.382
- Well, I don't know when he'll be back.
- It doesn't matter.

41:44.444 --> 41:46.651
You've been away at school, haven't you?

41:46.713 --> 41:48.954
- Came in to see your show last night.
- Really?

41:49.016 --> 41:50.757
- Liked it very much.
- Thank you.

41:50.817 --> 41:53.263
- I've seen all your shows.
- Both of them?

41:54.988 --> 41:57.298
Excuse me. Won't you sit down?

41:57.357 --> 42:00.236
I was just making some tea.
Would you like some?

42:00.293 --> 42:03.206
No, thank you. I had my tea today.

42:03.263 --> 42:05.539
- How are the folks?
- Fine. They'll be in soon.

42:05.599 --> 42:08.079
Well, I guess I'll go to the movie myself.

42:08.135 --> 42:09.773
They say it's a good picture.

42:09.836 --> 42:13.978
- Camille. Have you seen it?
- No, I haven't, but I'm going to.

42:14.041 --> 42:16.988
- Well, tell Ben to call me.
- All right.

42:17.844 --> 42:20.654
Oh, say, Dorothy, you wouldn't like
to see the movie with me?

42:20.714 --> 42:23.854
- Oh, thank you, but I'm afraid not.
- Why not?

42:23.917 --> 42:25.794
Well, you see, I...

42:25.852 --> 42:29.390
Well, I never go out with older men.

42:29.456 --> 42:31.732
- With what?
- You know what I mean.

42:31.792 --> 42:35.205
- All of Ben's friends are kind of...
- Kind of old men, huh?

42:35.262 --> 42:37.003
Well, I'm sure you understand.

42:37.064 --> 42:40.705
Oh, certainly. I understand perfectly.

42:41.201 --> 42:42.339
Good night.

42:44.938 --> 42:48.886
<i>That was really Black Sunday for me.
Shut out twice.</i>

42:48.942 --> 42:53.254
<i>Once because I was too young,
and once because I was too old.</i>

42:53.313 --> 42:57.989
<i>I pictured myself tragically wandering
around the globe for the rest of my days.</i>

42:58.652 --> 43:02.657
<i>And in my grief I was certainly
in the right frame of mind to see Camille.</i>

43:26.947 --> 43:29.860
<i>But I'd clean forgotten
that there was a big stage show,</i>

43:29.916 --> 43:32.089
<i>all built around one of our numbers.</i>

43:46.967 --> 43:50.471
<i>Remember the youth amid snow and ice</i>

43:50.537 --> 43:54.246
<i>Who bore the banner
