<i>That day I was very much alone.</i>

48:34.487 --> 48:36.626
<i>Larry was away seeing Peggy, and I hoped</i>

48:36.689 --> 48:40.000
<i>things were going a lot better for him
than they had for me.</i>

48:41.528 --> 48:44.008
Now you've really got me surrounded.

48:44.063 --> 48:47.010
A bolted door, a Rodgers and Hart song.

48:47.066 --> 48:48.943
What's the next twist to the plot?

48:49.002 --> 48:51.915
Well, that shouldn't be hard to guess.
It's the love scene.

48:51.971 --> 48:54.747
You know, where the fellow tells the girl
that she's like a Roman candle,

48:54.808 --> 48:58.722
a Greek chorus, an Italian gondola,
only here we are in Indianapolis.

48:58.778 --> 49:02.157
Then when he runs out of things to say,
instead of coming to the point,

49:02.215 --> 49:05.059
he reaches into his pocket
and hands her a prop.

49:08.488 --> 49:10.399
Go ahead. Try it on for size.

49:11.958 --> 49:13.335
Excuse me.

49:20.033 --> 49:22.570
What's the matter, Peggy?
Don't you want it?

49:22.669 --> 49:25.149
Sure, I want it. I want it very much.

49:26.339 --> 49:27.477
But I just can't.

49:27.540 --> 49:29.747
Hey, hey, hey, wait a minute,
will you, Peg? This is Larry Hart.

49:29.809 --> 49:31.789
Remember me?
The fellow who wants to marry you.

49:31.845 --> 49:35.054
Larry, that's just the trouble.

49:35.114 --> 49:36.252
What?

49:37.116 --> 49:41.360
I love you too much to fool you,
but I don't love you enough to marry you.

49:42.388 --> 49:46.530
- A little too much but not quite enough.
- Please don't, Larry.

49:46.593 --> 49:50.564
Look, you're a big success,
you're talented, you're funny and nice,

49:50.663 --> 49:52.734
and there's so much else in life for you.

49:52.799 --> 49:55.405
None of that seems important to me now.

49:55.468 --> 49:59.041
I only wish you were the guy.
I hate hurting you.

49:59.105 --> 50:02.484
No, it's not your fault. It's mine.

50:02.542 --> 50:05.853
It always hurts when you find out
you've been kidding yourself.

50:05.912 --> 50:08.825
And deep down,
I always knew I really wasn't the guy.

50:08.882 --> 50:10.691
I wanted it to be you.

50:10.750 --> 50:12.388
- So much.
- I knew.

50:13.419 --> 50:16.889
For me, your heart doesn't pound,
your stars don't sing,

50:16.956 --> 50:19.869
and your world doesn't stop.
That's why I'm not the guy.

50:19.926 --> 50:21.599
- Larry, where you going?
- Who knows?

50:21.661 --> 50:24.073
The thing is to go and go fast.

51:20.086 --> 51:22.088
Lexington 5400.

51:24.490 --> 51:26.299
Hello, Dick?

51:26.359 --> 51:27.895
Lorry is home.

51:33.666 --> 51:35.771
- Hiya, Mr. Hart.
- Hiya, Dick.

51:35.835 --> 51:39.715
- Well, what do you say?
- Oh, I'm fine.

51:39.772 --> 51:42.412
Missed you. Where've you been?

51:42.475 --> 51:45.513
Oh, went to a couple of places
I always wanted to see.

51:46.746 --> 51:49.522
- Did you see them real good?
- Yeah.

51:49.582 --> 51:51.186
I saw them great.

51:51.250 --> 51:53.127
- How's the show doing?
- Selling out.

51:53.186 --> 51:55.666
Oh, that's fine. Anything else new?
What's new?

51:55.722 --> 51:58.464
Oh, nothing much.
Been fooling around with a tune or two.

51:58.524 --> 51:59.696
That's good.

52:00.660 --> 52:02.162
What's wrong, Larry?

52:03.563 --> 52:05.167
The usual thing.

52:05.231 --> 52:08.542
The love song is slowing up
the show a bit.

52:08.601 --> 52:10.012
- Anything I can do?
- No.

52:10.069 --> 52:12.413
No, everything's been done.

52:12.472 --> 52:14.952
No more love songs. That's all. No.

52:15.008 --> 52:18.319
Just those fast, bright things
from here on in, huh? Huh?

52:18.378 --> 52:19.686
Larry, I hate to see you like this.

52:19.746 --> 52:24.058
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to get lost.
I didn't mean to get everybody in a storm.

52:24.117 --> 52:26.825
- It's all over.
- It's all over.

52:27.920 --> 52:30.457
<i>Finie la guerre</i>. The boat has sailed.

52:30.990 --> 52:33.300
It's all over. Well...

52:34.260 --> 52:35.933
What do we do next, huh?

52:35.995 --> 52:37.941
- Feel like working?
- Sure. Sure, anything.

52:37.997 --> 52:39.271
Make me an offer.

52:39.332 --> 52:41.107
- We got a wire from Cochran in London.
- Yeah?

52:41.167 --> 52:43.511
- He wants us to bring our show over.
- The Girl Friend?

52:43.569 --> 52:46.072
- That's right.
- Oh. Gosh.

52:46.139 --> 52:48.016
- Cochran, huh?
- Right away.

52:48.074 --> 52:50.782
Oh, good. Is it a good deal?

52:52.712 --> 52:55.420
- What do we think about it?
- I'm ready.

52:56.916 --> 52:58.862
